The paper deals with sublinear time algorithms for analyzing the cluster structure of graphs, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of conductance-based definitions for measuring the quality of clusters and the cluster structure also suggests a connection to statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the development of local algorithms for analyzing graphs with noisy partial information is a problem that can be relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
